%% Shipment lifecycle — generated from app/services/shipment_service.py::_is_transition_allowed
%% This is the AUTHORITATIVE transition map currently enforced in code.
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> created : POST /shipments (client_id, warehouses, weight, volume)

    created --> ready : status_update
    created --> cancelled : status_update

    ready --> assigned : POST /assign (driver+vehicle) OR status_update
    ready --> cancelled : status_update

    assigned --> in_transit : status_update (pickup confirmed)
    assigned --> cancelled : status_update

    in_transit --> delivered : status_update (+ POD event)
    in_transit --> failed : status_update (delivery exception)
    in_transit --> returned : status_update (return initiated)

    delivered --> [*]
    cancelled --> [*]
    returned --> [*]
    failed --> [*]

    note right of assigned
      assign_driver_and_vehicle() sets assigned_at and,
      if status in {created, ready}, promotes to assigned.
      Exclusivity: a driver/vehicle cannot hold two ACTIVE
      shipments (created/ready/assigned/in_transit).
    end note

    note right of delivered
      Terminal states (no outgoing transitions):
      delivered, cancelled, returned, failed.
      delivered_at / cancelled_at stamped on entry.
    end note
